// expect-fail: E1001
// expect-msg: column 13
//
// advance() must count Unicode codepoints in UTF-16 code units, not raw
// bytes (nexus-rsgp).  The string literal "コ" is 3 UTF-8 bytes but 1
// UTF-16 code unit.
//
// After lexing `let a = "コ" `, the ! token is at column 13 with UTF-16
// counting (each ASCII char + 1 UTF-16 unit for コ).  With raw byte
// counting, the same position would wrongly appear as column 15.
let a = "コ" !
